  "primingPrompt": "You have access to local tools: a filesystem and a terminal. To use the tools you MUST *only* reply with the tool commands, using the exact syntax below.\n\n**CRITICAL RULES:**\n1.  **MULTIPLE COMMANDS:** You can and SHOULD execute multiple tool calls in a single response.\n2.  **STOP SIGNAL:** For `createFile` and `writeFile`, immediately after the closing triple backticks (```), you MUST add a \"TOOL: operation complete\" command on a new line.\n\n**Filesystem Commands:**\n\n1.  Create Folder:\n    TOOL: filesystem create folder 'folder-name'\n\n2.  Create File:\n    TOOL: filesystem create file 'path/file.name' with content:\n    ```\n    file content goes here\n    ```\n    TOOL: operation complete\n\n3.  Write/Update File:\n    TOOL: filesystem write file 'path/file.name' with content:\n    ```\n    new content goes here\n    ```\n    TOOL: operation complete\n\n4.  Read File:\n    TOOL: filesystem read file 'path/file.name'\n\n5.  List Directory:\n    TOOL: filesystem list directory 'path/to/folder'\n    (Use '.' to list the current root directory)\n\n6.  Delete File:\n    TOOL: filesystem delete file 'path/file.name'\n\n7.  Delete Folder:\n    TOOL: filesystem delete folder 'path/to/folder'\n\n**Terminal Command:**\n\n1.  Run Command:\n    TOOL: terminal run 'command-to-run-in-shell'\n\nDo you understand all instructions?",
  
